x10.matrix

Class SymDense

  • x10.matrix.Matrix
    • x10.matrix.DenseMatrix
      • x10.matrix.SymDense

  • public class SymDense
extends DenseMatrix
    Declaration: SymDense extends x10.matrix.DenseMatrix.
    The symmetric dense matrix is derived from dense matrix. It inherits the memory layout of the
dense matrix instance.  Therefore, it complies with
BLAS symmetric matrix. Only the lower part of matrix data is referenced.

    
Result of cell-wise operations on symmetric matrix is stored in dense instances.
Most cellwise operations resort to the super dense class's operations without
optimization.

        x10$matrix$SymDense$$this$x10$matrix$SymDense
        

        public final SymDense x10$matrix$SymDense$$this$x10$matrix$SymDense()
        

        Declaration: x10$matrix$SymDense$$this$x10$matrix$SymDense(): x10.matrix.SymDense{self==this(:x10.matrix.SymDense)}.
        The symmetric dense matrix is derived from dense matrix. It inherits the memory layout of the
dense matrix instance.  Therefore, it complies with
BLAS symmetric matrix. Only the lower part of matrix data is referenced.

        
Result of cell-wise operations on symmetric matrix is stored in dense instances.
Most cellwise operations resort to the super dense class's operations without
optimization.
